[2] Angola, Lunda Norte province
Date: Mon 30 May 2016
Source: Aman Alliance [edited]
http://www.aman-alliance.org/mednews/daily/Lusa%20-%20Business%20News%20-%20Angola%20Yellow%20fever%20appears%20in%20another%20province.txt


Yellow fever appears in another province
----------------------------------------
The cause of the outbreak of fever like symptoms in the Guango region of the Angolan province of Lunda Norte is yellow fever following tests carried out by the National Health Laboratory of Luanda. The Lunda Norte Provincial Health Director, Buagica Mambelo, told Lusa Monday [30 May 2016] that confirmation had come last week and that the Ministry of Health had already dispatched a team of specialists to the region to analyse the extent of the outbreak.

Mambelo maintained that the situation was under control, with vaccination already ongoing and due to extend throughout the province following 4 cases of local transmission out of 9 suspected cases.

The diamond mining province of Lunda Norte had been yellow fever free until 2 weeks ago with the 10-day long vaccination campaign reported to have covered 10 553 persons in the meanwhile. Angola has been coping with a yellow fever epidemic since December 2015, 1st breaking out in the capital of Luanda but having since spread to other provinces and claiming in the region of 300 lives thus far.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The spread of yellow fever to previously unaffected provinces is worrisome. The prompt vaccination of 10 553 individuals is encouraging, but the population of the province is not stated, so one does not know the proportion of the population is covered. Because the province is a diamond mining area bordered on the north and the east by the Congo DR, one might assume that there is significant cross-border movement or workers with the related risk of movement of YF virus-infected individuals.

A map showing the location of Lunda Norte province can be accessed at http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/africa/angola.gif. - Mod.TY]

